{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T09:15:51.144Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Batched Computation — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Batched Computation Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batched computation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the technique of processing multiple training samples (a batch) simultaneously in parallel on the GPU rather than processing them one-by-one sequentially."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In deep learning, "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "batch size"}, {"type": "text", "text": " refers to the number of training examples processed at once before updating model weights. GPU processes the entire batch in parallel, leveraging its 16,000+ cores to compute operations on all samples simultaneously."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Batched Computation Matters in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Batched computation is the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "foundation of efficient GPU training"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for large models:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Aspect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sequential Processing"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Batched Processing"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "GPU utilization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Low (underutilized cores)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "High (all cores active)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Speed"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Slow (one sample at a time)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fast (all samples in parallel)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Memory"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Lower usage"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Higher usage (but efficient)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Training time"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Days/weeks"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Hours"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A larger batch size allows the GPU to process more data in parallel, "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "increasing efficiency"}, {"type": "text", "text": " significantly."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Batched Computation Works"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Parallel Processing Model"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Batch Size = 64\n\nGPU (16,000 cores)\n├── Core 1     → Sample 1\n├── Core 2     → Sample 2\n├── Core 3     → Sample 3\n├── ...        → ...\n├── Core 64    → Sample 64\n└── Core 65-16000 → Additional parallel operations (matrix math)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Instead of waiting for one task to finish before starting another, GPU executes "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "independent operations simultaneously"}, {"type": "text", "text": " across all 64 samples in the batch."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In PyTorch"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch\nimport torch.nn as nn\n\n# Model\nmodel = nn.Linear(784, 10)\n\n# Batch size\nbatch_size = 64\n\n# Create batch of data (all on GPU)\ninput_batch = torch.randn(batch_size, 784).to('cuda')\n\n# GPU processes ALL 64 samples in parallel\noutput_batch = model(input_batch)  # Batched computation\n\n# output_batch shape: [64, 10] (all predictions)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The GPU processes the entire batch simultaneously rather than sequentially."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In TensorFlow/Keras"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import tensorflow as tf\n\n# Model\nmodel = tf.keras.Sequential([\n    tf.keras.layers.Dense(256, activation='relu', input_shape=(784,)),\n    tf.keras.layers.Dense(10)\n])\n\n# Batch of data\ninput_batch = tf.random.normal([64, 784])\n\n# GPU processes batch in parallel\noutput_batch = model(input_batch, training=True)  # Batched computation"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Batch Size Selection"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Recommended Batch Sizes"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "GPU Type"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "VRAM"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Batch Size Range"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use Case"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Small GPUs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4–8 GB"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "16–64"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Memory-constrained"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "High-End GPUs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "24+ GB (RTX 4090)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "256–1024"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fully utilize GPU"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "AI Inference"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Any"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1–8"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Low latency, real-time"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Most Applications"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Any"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "32–128"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best balance"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Effects of Batch Size"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Batch Size"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Memory Usage"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Training Stability"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Speed"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Small (1–16)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Low"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Stable"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Slower"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Medium (32–128)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Balanced"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Stable"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fast"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Large (256–1024)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "High"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Can be unstable"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fastest"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Trade-offs"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Small batch"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Less memory, stable training, slower\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Large batch"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Fully utilizes GPU, faster, but can cause overfitting and instability"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "GPU Limitations"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Pipeline Saturation"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "GPU has limited pipelines (~12)\n\nBatch Size < 12:  Partial utilization\nBatch Size = 12:  Full utilization (saturated)\nBatch Size > 12:  No additional speedup (already saturated)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A GPU can only do calculations in parallel "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "up to the number of pipelines it has"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". Even with a batch size of one, there's plenty of opportunity for vectorization/parallelism."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Memory Bottleneck"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Memory usage depends on:\n- Batch size (bigger batch = more memory)\n- Model size (larger model = more memory)\n- Computation history (autograd stores gradients)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "bottleneck is GPU memory"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — if your model is large, autograd must store all computation history, and bigger batches use more memory."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Optimizing Batched Computation"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. CUDA Streams + Batch Size"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "To "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "fully utilize high-end GPUs"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", use a combination of:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Optimal strategy for RTX 4090 (24GB VRAM)\n# 1. Increase batch size to maximize parallel computation\nbatch_size = 256  # or higher if VRAM allows\n\n# 2. Use multiple CUDA streams for different workloads\nstream1 = torch.cuda.Stream()\nstream2 = torch.cuda.Stream()\n\n# 3. Overlap data transfers with computation\nwith stream1:\n    input1 = data1.to('cuda')  # Transfer while computing\n    output1 = model(input1)\n\nwith stream2:\n    input2 = data2.to('cuda')  # Transfer while computing\n    output2 = model(input2)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Benefits"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Allows data to be copied from CPU to GPU while computations are ongoing\n- Handles different workloads simultaneously"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. Balance Batch Size and Streams"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Balance the two:\n- Running too many streams with large batch sizes → memory bottleneck\n- Optimal: Find sweet spot between batch size and number of streams"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. Continuous Batching (LLM Inference)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Synchronous batching (bad):\nCPU batch prep → GPU compute → Idle gap → CPU batch prep → GPU compute\n\nAsynchronous continuous batching (good):\nCPU prep batch 1\nGPU compute batch 1\nCPU prep batch 2 (while GPU computing)\nGPU compute batch 2 (while CPU prep batch 3)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CUDA Streams and Events enable "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "overlapping CPU and GPU workloads"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", eliminating idle gaps."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Practical Guidelines"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Finding Optimal Batch Size"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Try different batch sizes and measure performance\nfor batch_size in [16, 32, 64, 128, 256]:\n    input_batch = torch.randn(batch_size, 784).to('cuda')\n    \n    # Measure forward pass time\n    start = torch.cuda.Event(enable_timing=True)\n    end = torch.cuda.Event(enable_timing=True)\n    \n    start.record()\n    output = model(input_batch)\n    end.record()\n    \n    torch.cuda.synchronize()\n    time = start.elapsed_time(end)\n    print(f\"Batch size {batch_size}: {time}ms\")"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Avoiding Memory Overflow"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Check available memory before large batch\nif torch.cuda.get_device_properties(0).total_memory < needed_memory:\n    batch_size = batch_size // 2  # Reduce batch size\n    print(f\"Reduced batch size to {batch_size}\")"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Large batch size can cause "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "memory overflow, leading to crashes"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental Model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Think of batched computation as "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "a restaurant kitchen"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Single chef (CPU)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Cooks one dish at a time"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Kitchen with 16,000 workers (GPU)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Cooks 64 dishes simultaneously"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch size"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Number of dishes on the order (64)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Parallel cooking"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Each worker cooks one dish part"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Overlap"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Prep next batch while cooking current batch (CUDA streams)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batched computation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Process multiple samples simultaneously in parallel on GPU"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch size"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Number of training examples processed at once"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Parallel"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": GPU processes entire batch simultaneously, not sequentially"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "16,000+ cores"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": RTX 4090 enables massive parallel computation"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Efficiency"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Larger batch size increases GPU efficiency"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Small batch (1–16)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Less memory, stable, slower"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Medium batch (32–128)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Best balance for most applications"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Large batch (256–1024)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Maximizes GPU, fastest, but can overfit/unstable"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Small GPUs (4–8GB)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Use batch 16–64"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "High-end GPUs (24GB+)